        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1949-11-02T18:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1949-11-02T18:00:00-05:00" n="1234" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1234">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">123 Ward, Angus I.: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Consul General at Peiping</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Clubb</hi>
                    </persName>)<note n="35" xml:id="d1234fn35">Repeated to the Ambassador in the
                        Soviet Union as telegram No. 814.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1949-11-02T18:00:00-05:00">November 2, 1949—6 p. m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>766. Dept considering instructing Moscow approach Sov FonOff outlining general
                    circumstances re ConGen Mukden and requesting Sovs exercise good offices
                    ascertain reasons continued Commie failure permit Ward and staff depart and to
                    facilitate departure. Ur comments wld be appreciated.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Acheson</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
